ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W2_WildLifeSanctuary

Class Name: WildLifeSanctuary

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving with Abstract Classes

Estimated Time: 60–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 65 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a wildlife sanctuary monitoring system using an abstract Animal class and multiple child classes.
The program should process daily care, update animal health, count critical animals, find the lowest-health animal,
and classify animals by care type.

Requirements
- Create an abstract Animal parent class.
- Create Bird, Mammal, and Reptile child classes.
- Override provideCare() and getCareType() in each child class.
- Store different child objects in one Animal[] array.
- Use helper methods to process care, count critical animals, find the lowest-health animal, and filter by care type.

Learning Objective
Practice abstract classes, abstract methods, overriding, polymorphism, arrays, loops, conditions, and object state updates.